ID=989.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Pets, Riposte and Enrage</span><hr size=1> To my knowledge, pets are (almost?) immune to ripostes from mobs. An enraging mob will riposte every attack on it from the front, and we know how fast pets die to this.<br>
<br>
My question now is, does anyone know why this happens? Of course a hasted pet attacks really quick and often, but if it was immune (or near) to ripostes it should be no problem for a pet to live through an enrage (or at least live long enough to be called off). Is enrage anything special so that the pets low vulnerability to ripostes doesnt work there?<br>
<br>
I would also be interested to see to which degree pets can avoid ripostes, has anyone ever taken any data on this?<br>
<br>
Izudin<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lordgojirax>LordGojirax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 513<br> <font color=#333333>(2/19/03 7:38:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=989.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jackntracie.com/images/gojhead.jpg width=98 height=126></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pets, Riposte and Enrage</span><hr size=1> Riposte is only good from about a 90 degree arc in front of the mobs.<br>
<br>
Put your pet to the side or back of a mob and you are safe from Riposte/Enrage.<br>
<br>
Good tanks will reposition mobs to keep the pets at it's back.<br>
<br>
If the tank in your group isn't doing this, request that they do.<br>
<br>
Positioning your pet on a raid level mob is also a good tactic to get used to, both for Enrage and for controling which way they push the mobs.<br>
<br>
I've never personally heard of pets being in any way immune or near immune to riposte though.<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.jackntracie.com/images/gojirax.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balasarius>Balasarius</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master of Italics</span><br>  Posts: 401<br> <font color=#333333>(2/19/03 9:00:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=989.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pets, Riposte and Enrage</span><hr size=1> Aye, pets are &quot;immune / near immune&quot; to riposte.  They implemented that about 6-9 months ago, I think.<br>
<br>
Before this change, it was most unwise to use pets against Venril Sathir.  Since the change my pet easily survives the fight with VS and takes no damage regardless of positioning.<br>
<br>
They are definitely not immune to enrage, though, hehe.<br>
<br>
I think that, simply, normal riposte and enrage work differently.<br>
