<br>
We all know that a full health pet (in a group situation where pet does not have aggro) will be eaten alive on an enraged mob if you don't back it off or if it does not hit from behind.<br>
<br>
The technical explanation is that ENRAGE is an autoriposte to all hits the pet will land.<br>
<br>
Now, what I don't understand, is how a 3k+ hp pet can deal 3k damage in the 10 seconds or so the enrage lasts. Epic hits for 87, best 61+ pets hit for 83, how in the hell can that equal 3k+ damage in 10 seconds ?<br>
<br>
Does this mean the riposte (the autoriposte from enrage) is not the amount of damage you are doing each hit, but the mob's damage ? id est, your pet takes a &quot;normal&quot; mob-hit, therefore 200+ in PoP, for each hit it lands ?<br>
<br>
I never played a melee character, maybe some of you could enlighten me ... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=goladus>Goladus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Poobah Goladus</span><br>  Posts: 2712<br> <font color=#333333>(2/20/03 7:51:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=989.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://doug.feldmann.com/Sigurd.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pets, Riposte and Enrage</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Does this mean the riposte (the autoriposte from enrage) is not the amount of damage you are doing each hit, but the mob's damage ? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Yes, riposte is most definitely the Mob's hit.<br>
